\begin_layout Subsection
Benefits to Graduate Students
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Mastering computational `human capital' provides many benefits to graduate
 students:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Less friction and frustration when programming
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Tackle more challenging problems and write a better thesis
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Research which is easier to defend and reproduce
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
More citations for your research from publishing good, open code 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Better job placement upon graduation because you have a competitive advantage
 vis-a-vis the computationally unskilled
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
A well-paid `outside option' developing software if you choose not to continue
 your career in academia
\end_layout

